commentary: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, no run big appeal for caught behind and the finger's gone up, Duminy reviews straightaway. Back of length delivery coming to the batsman, Duminy shows the face of the bat and there's a sound as the ball passes the batsman but no signs of the ball hitting the bat, it went past the inside edge and the decision has been overturned. The sound was of the ball clipping Duminy's thigh pad and that's the first successful review of the series, says the commentator

The umpires felt that Misbah took far too long to signal the review so it's invalid now, Misbah has to go. This was the googly, lands outside off and Misbah was forward and very tentative in offering a shot, hits his thigh and Tahir was demanding in his appeal, the umpire took his time and gave him out, Misbah walked over in slow motion almost to Shafiq, discussion, too late Sir!
